From: Gaggery Tsai <gaggery.tsai@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2026 00:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] drm/i915/psr: handle Panel Replay full-line SU granularity

Panel Replay SU reports X granularity = 0xFFFF meaning full-line.
Without this, psr2_granularity_check() rejects PR SU because
2880 % 65535 != 0.

Signed-off-by: Gaggery Tsai <gaggery.tsai@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
@@ -1326,9 +1326,17 @@
 	const int crtc_hdisplay = crtc_state->hw.adjusted_mode.crtc_hdisplay;
 	const int crtc_vdisplay = crtc_state->hw.adjusted_mode.crtc_vdisplay;
 	u16 y_granularity = 0;
+	u16 w_granularity = intel_dp->psr.su_w_granularity;
+
+	/*
+	 * Panel Replay SU can report 0xFFFF meaning full-line granularity.
+	 * Substitute crtc_hdisplay so the modulo check passes.
+	 */
+	if (w_granularity == 0xFFFF)
+		w_granularity = crtc_hdisplay;
 
 	/* PSR2 HW only send full lines so we only need to validate the width */
-	if (crtc_hdisplay % intel_dp->psr.su_w_granularity)
+	if (crtc_hdisplay % w_granularity)
 		return false;
 
 	if (crtc_vdisplay % intel_dp->psr.su_y_granularity)
